					   <td>

			
			
			


<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">

		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Hotkey/Social Bar Guide</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:">Screach</a> | 
		            5/9/2001 3:22:42 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Hotkey/Social Bar Guide.<BR>
<BR>
As many of you know, I've seen plenty of material here of people asking for help about hotkeys and socials.  Mainly Bards looking for a way to switch their instruments with their weapons, or vise versa.  Well, after reading through tons of great work posted on this website saying, &quot;Yes, it can be done, but we're not going to show or tell you&quot;, it gets frustrating, especially if you're new and don't want to spend all that time figuring out if this combination will work or not.  Unfortunately, I too, don't know how to do switch weapons or instruments.  So if you know, please post how to do it properly here, or give an example.  It would mean a lot to all of us.  Each paragraph begins with a &quot;mini-title&quot; in quotes.  This will help if you're just looking for a specfic part or topic.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;The Prelude&quot;  The headaches that come as a result of not knowing how to hotkey or make a social is insufferable.  I've read many sad stories of people losing there pets, their lives, and their weapons and instruments just because they don't know how to make a social or a hotkey properly, if at all.  Let's face it, having to type all your commands in or to use your mouse to switch from weapon/instrument or instrument/weapon or even just to click on your spells can cost you your life.  It brings a tear to my eye, knowing I'm amoung their ranks.  But fret no more!  I'm here to bring to light what other's take lightly.  <BR>
<BR>
&quot;The Warning&quot;  Now, bare in mind, setting up socials or hotkeys will not solve all your problems, espeically if your stunned and your socials/hotkeys have not yet finished.  This is only meant to help you set up your keys so you can use them &quot;wisely&quot;.  Many people sometimes curse socials/hotkeys because they got stunned and their macros didn't finish, so they couldn't cast the last spell on time or do whatever it was they needed to do to save their life or their pets.  It's very riskey, so use caution.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;To Make or Change a Social Bar&quot;  First, make sure your Main Box or Main Window is open if you're on the full screen mode.  If not, press Alt + M in full screen mode to make it reappear if you've left that command unaltered.  Then, in the window that has your &quot;Ablities,&quot; &quot;Combat,&quot; and &quot;Social&quot; bars, click on &quot;Social.&quot;  A list of pre-typed socials appear starting on page 1.  There are twelve bars per page.  Just by left-clicking on these bars, many useful commands are automatically completed for you without having to type them in.  &quot;Yes, we know, but how to we change them or view them?&quot;  This applies to all the social bars, including the blank ones.  Simply right-click on them and a dialog box appears in front of you.  The top bar is the title with room for about six characters to help you identify the bar.  In the next five lines provided, you can type in a command just like the main dialog window where all your dialog appears.  I've heard some say only one command can be issued per line, but I've read contrary, like &quot;/pause 30, /cast 1&quot;.  This setup, which is only on one line, is suppose to do two commands,cast whatever spell or song you have in slot 1, and then pause for 3 seconds.  It's confusing because it's backwards, but this does, in fact, work.  You can use all these lines to make and mix many commands.  Give it a title and click done, and it appears on your social bar list.  You have 10 pages with 12 customizable social bars each that you can flip back and forth on.  This gives you 120 of them social bars to play with.  <BR>
<BR>
&quot;Small Glitch in Social Window&quot;  Sometimes you won't be able to see the last two bar titles on the bottom of the screen.  This is because you have the window too close the bottom of the screen.  Raise it up just a little, and that should solve your problem.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;To Make or Change a Hotkey&quot;  First, make sure your Hotkey box or Hotkey Window is open if you're on the full screen mode.  If not, press Alt + H in full screen mode to make it reappear if you've left that command unaltered.  Then, to make your own custom hotkey, you must have first made a social bar, with a few exceptions.  Hotkeys are assigned, except for a few like Persona, and your skills under combat and ablilities, from your social bar.  You must place the desired bar, whether it be Persona, or something like it, or a social bar, in one of the hotkey boxes.  To do this, left-click and hold the mouse button over the bar you want to make a hotkey until they pop out and start following your mouse.  Yeah, pretty cool, huh?  Then place them in the hotkey box.  Now all you have to do is decide where you want them.  The most upper-left box is number one, and goes left to right.  In other words, the one that's to the right of it is number two.  The onle below the first one is number three, and the one to the right of that one is number four, and so on.  As long as you haven't changed the user defined keys to something else, that's the order they'll be in.  You'll also only be able to see all of them in full screen mode.  To get rid of a hotkey, simply right-click on it.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Pets&quot;  Yes, it's true.  You can make social bars, and then hotkeys for your very own pet.  These come in handy, especially if you don't want to type it all out.  Your fingers would cramp from typing too fast, plus one wrong error in your command and the whole sentence becomes something you say instead of something you want to happen.  It's only funny to those who see it, not to those who experience it.  As far as I know, all the /pet commands work, such as &quot;/pet as you were&quot;, &quot;/pet attack &lt;target&gt;&quot;, &quot;/pet back off&quot;, &quot;/pet follow me&quot;, &quot;/pet get lost&quot; and all the other commands that go with &quot;/pet &lt;command&gt;&quot;.  Makes typing very easy.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;The Commands&quot;  Sadly, I don't know all of the commands that can fit into a social bar.  Although not here, I may post a Command guide shortly, including the emotions you can show.  I do know though that most of the commands you type in the Main dialog box will work in the soical bars, such as /auction, /em, /pets, /say, and a few other popular ones.  /pause is unique to the social bars, though, as I've never heard anyone type it in, and I don't think they ever will need to.  If you want to post something about a command or combination you think is cool, let's hear it.  I'm open to new combinations and mixes.  I think it'll be neat.  Don't be afraid of giving examples too.  I know they may be long and drawn out sometimes, but they can help teach us all how cool you are, and how to do the same thing.<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Conclusion&quot;  Well, I hope you learned a little more about how to play EQ a little bit better.  I hope I wasn't too confusing.  Let me know what you think, and if I need to change anything.  Well, have fun!<BR>
<BR>
Screach lvl 10 Bard
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
