				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				i actually read this on this site somewhere. a warrior guide from a troll warrior?? <BR>
this this may be the site. Great write up.<BR>
<BR>
http://gameznet.com/eq/class/warrior2.html<BR>
<BR>
get a new set of hotkeys. I.E.<BR>
sense heading...<BR>
<BR>
ok.  now make sure you have 2 open main inventory slots. hot key them. now hot key primary and off hand from inventory screen.  say 1 and 2 are inventory 3 is primary 4 is secondary.<BR>
<BR>
to take your secondary weapon and replace with shield do this...  <BR>
place a shield in one of the inventory slots. lets say 1 to make it simple.<BR>
now make a hot key from socials.<BR>
<BR>
/doability 4<BR>
/doability 1<BR>
/doability 4<BR>
<BR>
this will remove secondary weapon or item onto cursor, then, places it into shield's inventory slot.  then this places the shield into secondary slot.  BUT... you would have to remember whats where.  i Believe that the hotkeys would show the items in each spot.<BR>
<BR>
so say your running.  press 5(if you places the 4 1 4 social on this hotkey) then when your ready to get back into combat, press 5 once more to have that offhand item back in its origonal slot.<BR>
<BR>
don't count on this. i haven't tried it yet. but it might just work for you.   try it out.<BR>
<BR>
check out the link up top. thats got some serious good points on warriors.
